   <pb facs="29"/>
   <head>An Admonition.</head>
   <p>VNto such, as haue none op<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>portunitie to saie the whole Psalter together, it is good that they faie the first v. pe<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>titions one daie, and the second v. another day, and the last v. ano<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ther day, &amp; so in three dayes they shal say y<seg rend="sup">e</seg> whole Psalter. But els if they may haue cōuenient time, it is better to say the xv. principal petitions euery day, &amp; ech of them x. times, with <hi>In nomine Iesu,</hi> in y<seg rend="sup">e</seg> beginning, <hi>Pater nost. Aue Maria.</hi> &amp; at euery fifth, like as it is writē in the boke, with <hi>Dominus noster, Pater noster. Aue Maria. Credo.</hi>
   </p>
</div>
